rget corporation valued at  billion through the purchase of stock and derivatives his funds now own a  stake in december  his funds held a  stake in borders group and on december   ackman indicated he would finance a buyout of barnes  noble for usm on january   the fund disclosed a  ownership stake in general growth properties ggp according to documents filed with the sec becoming the secondlargest shareholder behind brookfield asset management the fund was betting on the company to go bankrupt in a way that would leave its shareholders intact in november  pershing square helped the company emerge from chapter  bankruptcy protection as of august  the fund holds beneficial ownership of  percent of general growths stock in  pershing square reported having taken large ownership stakes in jc penney and canadian pacific railway in july  ackman acknowledged to cnbc that he had acquired shares in procter  gamble worth approximately  billion a  stake in the company with the idea of taking an activist role within the corporation pershing square later reduced its stake in procter  gamble which was valued at around  million by the end of  in the first quarter of  the hedge fund experienced its biggestever quarterly loss of  due in part to its  stake in valeant pharmaceuticals international ackman who joined valeants board in march  commented on the companys  loss since august  stating “this is going to be a badly scraped knee that may even require stitches but it is not life threatening we should be able to recover the lions share of our investment — if not all of it — over time in september  pershing square continued its investment in fast food by buying a  stake in chipotle mexican grill herbalifeedit see also bill ackman herbalife short in december  ackman announced that the firm had made a  billion short bet against herbalife a maker of weightloss and vitamin supplements calling the company a pyramid scheme after activist billionaire investor carl icahn bought a stake in the company in january  the share price rose nearly  and the investment was seen by analysts as the worst investment ever made by the firm after a persistent political and grassroots campaign funded by ackman and the firm the federal trade commission initiated a civil investigation into herbalife causing its stock to drop enough that by march  pershing square was nearly even on their bet in april  reuters reported that according to its sources the fbi conducted a probe into herbalife and reviewed documents obtained from the companys former distributors in march  us district judge dale fischer dismissed a suit filed by herbalife investors alleging the company is operating an illegal pyramid scheme on march   it reported that ackman was under investigation by federal prosecutors and the fbi ackman was quoted that he would not back down from his claims against herbalife platform specialty products corporationedit as of june  pershing square is the largest institutional holder of the shares of platform specialty products corporation nyse pah owning a  stake pershing first disclosed the position in january  shortly after platform debuted on the new york stock exchange subsequently in april  platform announced a deal to acquire the agrochemicals business of chemtura for approximately  billion agriphar another agricultural specialty chemicals company agreed in august  to become the third company to join the platform umbrella in april  ackman singled out platform specialty products in the outsider presentation which discusses optimal methods of capital allocation referencesedit  bill ackman bio returns net worth insider monkey retrieved  april    markus krebsz  june  securitisation and structured finance post credit crunch a best practice deal lifecycle guide john wiley and sons pp – isbn  retrieved  august    joseph a mccahery erik p m vermeulen  november  corporate governance of nonlisted companies oxford university press us pp – isbn  retrieved  august    a b philip cogga